docs.lead_paragraph: The Somerset County Teachers' Institute was organized on Monday, at 11 o'clock, with thirty teachers in attendance, and the number increasing at every sessoin. Mr. O. C. CONE was chosen President, and the necessary officers appointed, and arrangements made to process to earnest business. At 2 o'clock his Excellence, Governor PHICE was escorted to the room, and pronounced an excellent and appropriate address,

docs.lead_paragraph: Some five thousand emigrants, hailing from various German and British ports, have arrived in New-York within the past week. They were for the most part belonging to the respectable and intelligent class, were very healthy, with scarcely an exception, and brought with them considerable means, the accumulations of industry in their native land.

docs.lead_paragraph: The first class graduated from the University of Vermont in 1804,--consisting of four persons, three of whom, CHARLES ADAMS of this town, I JUSTUS P. WHEELER of Arkansas, and WHEELER BARNES of Oneida County, N.Y., still survive, and were present at the Semi-Centennial Celebration of their Alma Mater which has just taken place. en ptace.
